Installation (for Ubuntu):
    * sudo aptitude install python2.7 python-setuptools git
    * sudo aptitude python-psycopg2 / sudo aptitude install python-mysql
    * sudo easy_install pip
    * sudo pip install virtualenv

    * virtualenv --no-site-packages VIRTUAL_ENV_DIR
    * source VIRTUAL_ENV_DIR/bin/activate
    * git clone git://github.com/sergkop/nabludatel.git CODE_DIR
    * pip install -r CODE_DIR/requirements.txt

    * edit settings.py
    * make sure that propriate media directories (static/, media/) are writable

    * 'python manage.py syncdb --all' (agree to create superuser)
    * python manage.py migrate --fake

    * Log in into admin interface (http://.../admin/) and set proper domain name in the entry of Sites model

    * lighttpd or 'python manage.py runserver' for development purposes (with proper virtualenv)
